 And maybe some of us in this room have the privilege of being in that position,

242
00:13:24,740 --> 00:13:29,440
 that God has blessed you with many, many great resources.

243
00:13:29,440 --> 00:13:33,000
 And you know that you've been blessed by God in this way.

244
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:36,600
 And if it is you, praise God and amen.

245
00:13:36,900 --> 00:13:40,500
 Right. God has blessed you, and that's a beautiful thing.

246
00:13:40,500 --> 00:13:44,660
 Maybe some of you in this room

247
00:13:44,660 --> 00:13:47,160
 have gone through a rough season in life.

248
00:13:47,160 --> 00:13:50,600
 Maybe you are sick and in need of healing.

249
00:13:50,600 --> 00:13:54,160
 Right. You reached a point where the doctor said, I can't do anything.

250
00:13:54,160 --> 00:13:56,400
 We can't do anything anymore.

251
00:13:56,400 --> 00:13:58,460
 But then you receive the healing.

252
00:13:58,460 --> 00:14:02,660
 Maybe you were in a deep depression and anxiety and you came to the Lord

253
00:14:02,660 --> 00:14:05,460
 and he gave you the peace that you were seeking.

254
00:14:05,460 --> 00:14:09,400
 Maybe you were in trouble and you came to Jesus and he gave you safety.

255
00:14:09,400 --> 00:14:11,660
 Maybe you were broke.

256
00:14:11,660 --> 00:14:15,000
 You came to him and he gave you money and the resources that you need.

257
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:19,760
 And you found when when you came to Jesus and put your prayers before him,

258
00:14:19,760 --> 00:14:22,200
 he helped you. He healed you.

259
00:14:22,200 --> 00:14:23,960
 He answered those prayers.

260
00:14:23,960 --> 00:14:27,760
 And this if this is you, praise God and amen.

261
00:14:27,760 --> 00:14:31,900
 God has blessed you in this way.

262
00:14:31,900 --> 00:14:34,700
 So it's important that you don't hear me wrong.

263
00:14:34,700 --> 00:14:41,100
 God is an exceedingly generous God and he will meet all our needs.

264
00:14:41,100 --> 00:14:46,700
 Scripture promises us that those who seek him like no good thing.

265
00:14:46,700 --> 00:14:53,700
 It tells us that every good and perfect gift comes from the father of light.

266
00:14:53,700 --> 00:14:59,760
 He is described as our refuge in times of help when we are in trouble.

267
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:06,540
 And so church always bring your prayers and needs before the Lord.

268
00:15:06,540 --> 00:15:09,160
 Ask for his help.

269
00:15:09,160 --> 00:15:13,040
 Ask for him to be there for you and see how he answers those prayers.

270
00:15:13,040 --> 00:15:17,440
 The problem, though, however,

271
00:15:17,440 --> 00:15:20,960
 the problem comes when you only come to Jesus,

272
00:15:20,960 --> 00:15:25,300
 when you only come to the Lord, when you need these blessings in your time of need.

273
00:15:25,300 --> 00:15:30,600
 The problem comes when your needs and your hunger become the primary

274
00:15:30,600 --> 00:15:35,660
 or even the only motivation for seeking Jesus.

275
00:15:35,660 --> 00:15:41,960
 And this is the problem with this crowd of people that Jesus has just fed.

276
00:15:41,960 --> 00:15:44,260
 Right. He's seen them. He loved them.

277
00:15:44,260 --> 00:15:45,860
 He had compassion for them.

278
00:15:45,860 --> 00:15:50,040
 Right. When there was no way to get food, he feeds them in the most abundant

279
00:15:50,040 --> 00:15:52,340
 and miraculous way.

280
00:15:52,340 --> 00:15:54,600
 And after that, Jesus has gone off to rest.

281
00:15:54,600 --> 00:15:59,500
 And so he's gone off to take a break and he's gone to the other side of town

282
00:15:59,500 --> 00:16:00,900
 by walking on the water.

283
00:16:00,900 --> 00:16:03,160
 OK, that's a whole other story in itself.

284
00:16:03,160 --> 00:16:04,200
 He walks on the water.

285
00:16:04,200 --> 00:16:06,860
 And so people are wondering, where did Jesus go? Right.

286
00:16:06,860 --> 00:16:08,160
 Where is he? They're looking for him.

287
00:16:08,160 --> 00:16:11,500
 And they find him on the other side of town across the lake.

288
00:16:11,500 --> 00:16:17,240
 But we soon find out they're looking for him because they're not content.

289
00:16:17,240 --> 00:16:21,840
 They're looking for him, not because they're interested in who he is,

290
00:16:21,840 --> 00:16:28,200
 but because they want more of what they feel like he can give to them.

291
00:16:29,900 --> 00:16:33,100
 So Jesus knows this and he tells them this.

292
00:16:33,100 --> 00:16:38,300
 He says, you are looking for me not because you saw the signs I performed,

293
00:16:38,300 --> 00:16:42,200
 but because you ate the loaves and had your fill.

294
00:16:42,200 --> 00:16:44,700
 And now you want more. Right.

295
00:16:44,700 --> 00:16:47,340
 You fed me yesterday. Jesus, feed me more again. Right.

296
00:16:47,340 --> 00:16:48,640
 I want to see the same.

297
00:16:48,640 --> 00:16:50,840
 Give me more of that bread. Give me more of that fish.

298
00:16:50,840 --> 00:16:54,800
 So I repeat the question again.

299
00:16:54,800 --> 00:16:59,140
 What are you truly hungry for when you look for Jesus?

300
00:17:00,160 --> 00:17:02,440
 What are you hungry for?

301
00:17:02,440 --> 00:17:04,560
 Now, when it comes to things we're hungry for,

302
00:17:04,560 --> 00:17:07,260
 we're often willing to do a little bit of work

303
00:17:07,260 --> 00:17:10,840
 to get that thing right when we're hungry.

304
00:17:10,840 --> 00:17:13,660
 And in this case, it seems, you know, when it comes to a relationship with Jesus,

305
00:17:13,660 --> 00:17:16,000
 we start putting this mindset as well. Right.

306
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:20,860
 We said, well, in the case of blessings, if we if we do more for Jesus,

307
00:17:20,860 --> 00:17:24,700
 maybe he'll bless us more.

308
00:17:24,700 --> 00:17:27,760
 That's a very typical mindset we get stuck in as well.

309
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:32,740
 I know that in my some seasons of my life, I've gone through this

310
00:17:32,740 --> 00:17:35,540
 and I've times I feel like I'm still prone to it.

311
00:17:35,540 --> 00:17:38,440
 There's a one or a need that we have.

312
00:17:38,440 --> 00:17:42,660
 We bring it before the Lord and suddenly in that time period

313
00:17:42,660 --> 00:17:45,040
 become the most committed person in the world. Right.

314
00:17:45,040 --> 00:17:47,700
 We start making deals with Jesus. Oh, Jesus.

315
00:17:47,700 --> 00:17:51,500
 I'm going to read my Bible for three hours every day. Right.

316
00:17:51,500 --> 00:17:52,760
 I'm going to wake up in the morning.

317
00:17:52,760 --> 00:17:53,860
 I'm not going to check my phone.

318
00:17:53,860 --> 00:17:55,700
 I'm just going to pray on my knees.

319
00:17:55,700 --> 00:17:57,460
 I'm going to stop this bad habit.

320
00:17:57,460 --> 00:18:00,340
 I'm going to stop being so grumpy with my children.

321
00:18:00,340 --> 00:18:02,000
 I'll be kinder to my family.

322
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:04,340
 I'll even fast for 21 days. Right.

323
00:18:04,340 --> 00:18:09,060
 To to get God to answer that prayer, to meet that need, to open that door.

324
00:18:09,060 --> 00:18:12,660
 But as soon as that happens.

325
00:18:12,660 --> 00:18:15,500
 Your promises to him also fall flat.

326
00:18:15,500 --> 00:18:20,600
 It's easy.

327
00:18:20,600 --> 00:18:25,300
 It's easy to think and look like you have the right motives.

328
00:18:26,240 --> 00:18:29,400
 But in the end, your true reason you're coming to Jesus,

329
00:18:29,400 --> 00:18:35,840
 it's more rather what Jesus can do for you than seeking Jesus himself.

330
00:18:35,840 --> 00:18:44,300
 And it's easy to think we can earn our way even to God's blessings.

331
00:18:44,300 --> 00:18:47,100
 This is how the crowd reacts.

332
00:18:47,100 --> 00:18:49,660
 They ask him, you know, what can we do

333
00:18:49,660 --> 00:18:53,500
 to do the works God requires?

334
00:18:53,500 --> 00:18:55,700
 What can we do to get these blessings?

335
00:18:55,700 --> 00:18:58,440
 What can we do to get you to give us more stuff?

336
00:18:58,440 --> 00:19:03,360
 And this is an earthly and misguided approach to a heavenly teaching.

337
00:19:03,360 --> 00:19:07,240
 This is the mindset that the rich young ruler had when he comes to Jesus

338
00:19:07,240 --> 00:19:12,860
 and says, good teacher, what must I do in order to inherit eternal life?

339
00:19:12,860 --> 00:19:16,840
 And maybe some of you in this room can relate as well.

340
00:19:16,840 --> 00:19:21,300
 We feel like if we act right, we do the good things.

341
00:19:21,300 --> 00:19:22,900
 We'd be a good Christian.

342
00:19:22,900 --> 00:19:27,940
 We go to church, we serve, we give generously, we pray, we read the Bible.

343
00:19:27,940 --> 00:19:30,240
 We worship with our hands up.

344
00:19:30,240 --> 00:19:31,560
 We join a community group.

345
00:19:31,560 --> 00:19:33,300
 We do all these things.

346
00:19:33,300 --> 00:19:36,660
 However, you know, in your heart, the true motivation behind it

347
00:19:36,660 --> 00:19:41,100
 is not really because you believe or you want to get closer to Jesus.

348
00:19:41,100 --> 00:19:45,240
 You're not really interested in the deep, meaningful relationship to him.

349
00:19:45,240 --> 00:19:49,300
 The motivation even for doing all these things is that for God

350
00:19:49,300 --> 00:19:51,000
 somehow will see us and return.

351
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:52,960
 So, oh, yeah, there's a good boy. There's a good girl.

352
00:19:52,960 --> 00:19:55,440
 There's a good person. Here are some blessings.

353
00:19:55,440 --> 00:20:00,500
 And we begin to treat relationship with Jesus like a business transaction.

354
00:20:00,500 --> 00:20:04,500
 You know, I've invested this much time, I've invested this much energy

355
00:20:04,500 --> 00:20:06,860
 into doing your work, Jesus.

356
00:20:06,860 --> 00:20:11,400
 I want to see some heavenly ROI on this investment on mine. Right.

357
00:20:11,400 --> 00:20:15,800
 If this is our attitude, church,

358
00:20:15,800 --> 00:20:20,340
 I don't really think we can say we believe in Jesus truly.

359
00:20:21,740 --> 00:20:24,340
 If this is an attitude, right, what's the difference between that

360
00:20:24,340 --> 00:20:27,340
 and going off to different areas?

361
00:20:27,340 --> 00:20:31,800
 Like I said just now, heading, hedging your bet, hedging your bets

362
00:20:31,800 --> 00:20:35,260
 and going off to different things, seeking blessings for different resources

363
00:20:35,260 --> 00:20:36,700
 just to see what works.

364
00:20:36,700 --> 00:20:38,500
 I'll shake some fortune sticks here.

365
00:20:38,500 --> 00:20:39,760
 I'll spin the wheel there.

366
00:20:39,760 --> 00:20:43,860
 I'll come to church on Sunday and let's see which God chooses to bless me.

367
00:20:47,800 --> 00:20:51,360
 Jesus doesn't tell us there's anything that we need to do.

368
00:20:51,360 --> 00:20:56,660
 Actually, it's very subtle, but very important what he does here

369
00:20:56,660 --> 00:20:59,360
 because they ask him so good, what do we have to do?

370
00:20:59,360 --> 00:21:01,760
 What are some things we can do to get more blessings from you?

371
00:21:01,760 --> 00:21:05,760
 What are the works, plural, the many things, right?

372
00:21:05,760 --> 00:21:08,140
 If we do many things for you, maybe you'll bless us.

373
00:21:08,140 --> 00:21:11,460
 He responds, Actually, there's nothing you have to do,

374
00:21:11,460 --> 00:21:13,940
 but there is only one work.

375
00:21:14,800 --> 00:21:18,360
 And Jesus says this, The work of God is this,

376
00:21:18,360 --> 00:21:22,740
 to believe in the one he has sent.

377
00:21:22,740 --> 00:21:26,900
 The only work, the only thing we need to do.

378
00:21:26,900 --> 00:21:31,260
 Is to believe.

379
00:21:31,260 --> 00:21:34,500
 So do we believe, church, in Jesus?

380
00:21:34,500 --> 00:21:38,900
 Because believing is different.

381
00:21:38,900 --> 00:21:43,400
 Believing isn't just about a change of actions or behavior.

382
00:21:44,940 --> 00:21:48,640
 Believing means an entire changing of your heart,

383
00:21:48,640 --> 00:21:52,300
 as we've been saying for the past few weeks, from the inside out.

384
00:21:52,300 --> 00:21:58,660
 Believing means you embrace the fact that Jesus is who he says he is.

385
00:21:58,660 --> 00:22:02,300
 Believing means that you recognize your need,

386
00:22:02,300 --> 00:22:06,800
 like as we've been singing about today, for Jesus as your Lord and Savior.

387
00:22:06,800 --> 00:22:11,540
 That he died for your sins, but he rose again in victory over death.

388
00:22:12,600 --> 00:22:15,640
 Believing means that we don't change our behavior

389
00:22:15,640 --> 00:22:19,640
 because we're trying to get God to, you know, manipulate God to do something for us.

390
00:22:19,640 --> 00:22:25,200
 Believing means our heart has been most transformed by the Holy Spirit,

391
00:22:25,200 --> 00:22:29,400
 that we can't do anything else other than act out of love.

392
00:22:29,400 --> 00:22:34,160
 The love that God gives to us.

393
00:22:34,160 --> 00:22:37,940
 Believing, as Andrew said last week, means like Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego.

394
00:22:37,940 --> 00:22:41,800
 We have faith that Jesus is who he says he is.

395
00:22:42,160 --> 00:22:44,960
 And even if we end up in the fiery furnace,

396
00:22:44,960 --> 00:22:48,000
 our belief in him doesn't change.

397
00:22:48,000 --> 00:22:52,300
 Believing means even this.

398
00:22:52,300 --> 00:22:56,700
 It means even if following Jesus and giving up everything for him

399
00:22:56,700 --> 00:23:01,000
 didn't didn't lead to anything that the world would call blessings.

400
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:04,560
 In fact, often it might lead to more hardship,

401
00:23:04,560 --> 00:23:09,640
 more conflict, more persecution, more discomfort, more pain,

402
00:23:09,640 --> 00:23:13,560
 more suffering, heartache, betrayal, poverty, sacrifice.

403
00:23:13,560 --> 00:23:15,400
 Jesus himself said it right.

404
00:23:15,400 --> 00:23:17,460
 The world will hate you.

405
00:23:17,460 --> 00:23:21,500
 We will still continue to believe.

406
00:23:21,500 --> 00:23:24,860
 Do we have that kind of belief?

407
00:23:24,860 --> 00:23:30,800
 Believing means putting all our faith, not hedging our bets,

408
00:23:30,800 --> 00:23:33,800
 all our faith in Jesus.

409
00:23:36,540 --> 00:23:40,140
 Believing means also we need to let this go of this constantly

410
00:23:40,140 --> 00:23:42,960
 asking Jesus for more, for more, for more.

411
00:23:42,960 --> 00:23:47,200
 Right. How can you confirm to me, Jesus, that you are really true?

412
00:23:47,200 --> 00:23:49,340
 Right. This is, again, a very Hong Kong thing.

413
00:23:49,340 --> 00:23:53,140
 The the the the phenomenon of double confirmation.

414
00:23:53,140 --> 00:23:56,800
 Right. Before you make a commitment to something, show me more, Jesus.

415
00:23:56,800 --> 00:23:57,800
 Then maybe I'll commit.

416
00:23:57,800 --> 00:24:00,860
 Give me more blessings and then maybe I'll commit to you.

417
00:24:00,860 --> 00:24:03,200
 And this is what the crowd wants.

418
00:24:03,200 --> 00:24:07,200
 Show us more signs. Show us more signs.

419
00:24:07,200 --> 00:24:10,200
 OK, the crowd say you ask us to believe in you. Fine, then. OK.

420
00:24:10,200 --> 00:24:14,400
 What sign? This is what the crowd says to Jesus in John 630.

421
00:24:14,400 --> 00:24:19,460
 What sign then will you give that we might see it and believe you?

422
00:24:19,460 --> 00:24:24,700
 If you would just show us more signs, then we might put our trust in you.

423
00:24:24,700 --> 00:24:27,860
 Then we might live that life for you.

424
00:24:27,860 --> 00:24:30,500
 Jesus, though, has a different agenda.

425
00:24:31,160 --> 00:24:34,740
 You see, through these signs, he's trying to open our eyes.

426
00:24:34,740 --> 00:24:37,400
 Now, a sign is just a sign, right?

427
00:24:37,400 --> 00:24:40,940
 The sign, the point of the sign is to point to something greater,

428
00:24:40,940 --> 00:24:43,760
 point to something better.

429
00:24:43,760 --> 00:24:46,700
 Right. This is an important theme in John's gospel.

430
00:24:46,700 --> 00:24:51,160
 In the Gospel of John, there are six or seven signs that he highlights.

431
00:24:51,160 --> 00:24:55,360
 All these signs are miracles, but they are miracles, not just meant

432
00:24:55,360 --> 00:24:58,340
 to stun people and people like, wow, that was an amazing moment.

433
00:24:58,740 --> 00:25:02,460
 These signs, these miracles are meant to point towards

434
00:25:02,460 --> 00:25:05,600
 showing who Jesus really is.

435
00:25:05,600 --> 00:25:07,740
 OK, let's go through them quickly.

436
00:25:07,740 --> 00:25:12,740
 Right. John chapter two, when Jesus turns the water into wine.

437
00:25:12,740 --> 00:25:16,000
 Right. Water into wine. Amazing moment.

438
00:25:16,000 --> 00:25:19,700
 The bigger thing, though, it points to is Jesus's identity.

439
00:25:19,700 --> 00:25:23,000
 Jesus's confirmation as the new covenant,

440
00:25:23,000 --> 00:25:26,940
 the new blood that he's going to give to us at his death.

441
00:25:27,660 --> 00:25:30,400
 John, chapter four, the healing of the official son

442
00:25:30,400 --> 00:25:34,440
 shows Jesus's authority over sickness.

443
00:25:34,440 --> 00:25:38,660
 John, chapter five, the healing of the pool of Bethsaida

444
00:25:38,660 --> 00:25:42,140
 shows Jesus's authority over the Sabbath,

445
00:25:42,140 --> 00:25:44,640
 which the Jewish people held so preciously.

446
00:25:44,640 --> 00:25:47,800
 John, chapter six, the feeding of the 5000.

447
00:25:47,800 --> 00:25:49,900
 We'll get to that in a moment, OK?

448
00:25:49,900 --> 00:25:52,600
 Another story in John, chapter six, when he walks on the water,

449
00:25:52,600 --> 00:25:56,840
 shows Jesus's authority over all nature and all creation that he is.

450
00:25:57,040 --> 00:26:01,500
 He was present during creation, so he has authority over to walk on the water.

451
00:26:01,500 --> 00:26:05,900
 John, chapter 11 shows the raising of Lazarus from the dead,

452
00:26:05,900 --> 00:26:09,660
 which is supposed to point to his authority over death.

453
00:26:09,660 --> 00:26:15,740
 You see, there's always a bigger purpose of why Jesus chooses to bless us,

454
00:26:15,740 --> 00:26:20,800
 to show us his love and mercy and grace through these signs and wonders.

455
00:26:20,800 --> 00:26:23,900
 Yes, he wants to provide for you because he loves you.

456
00:26:24,600 --> 00:26:30,000
 But more than that, he wants to show us who he really is.

457
00:26:30,000 --> 00:26:34,640
 But if all we do is chase after these signs and these wonders

458
00:26:34,640 --> 00:26:39,160
 and these blessings, we will never be satisfied.

459
00:26:39,160 --> 00:26:44,460
 This is just the reality of our sinful human nature.

460
00:26:44,460 --> 00:26:49,000
 And so Jesus doesn't answer the crowds when they say, show us a sign.

461
00:26:49,000 --> 00:26:52,200
 Instead, he responds by saying these two things.

462
00:26:53,000 --> 00:26:59,000
 Do not work for the food that spoils, but for the food that endures to eternal life.

463
00:26:59,000 --> 00:27:03,560
 Why? Because your ancestors ate the manna in the wilderness.

464
00:27:03,560 --> 00:27:06,640
 Yet they still died.

465
00:27:06,640 --> 00:27:09,700
 So there's two problems here.

466
00:27:09,700 --> 00:27:12,200
 Jesus is trying to show us when we go after earthly,

467
00:27:12,200 --> 00:27:14,900
 when we go after these signs and these wonders all the time.

468
00:27:14,900 --> 00:27:20,240
 First thing is this food on this earth will spoil.

469
00:27:21,240 --> 00:27:24,540
 Meaning things of this world will get old.

470
00:27:24,540 --> 00:27:26,360
 They will be ruined.

471
00:27:26,360 --> 00:27:29,400
 I mean, just look at the iPhone, OK?

472
00:27:29,400 --> 00:27:31,340
 Like there's another iPhone coming out.

473
00:27:31,340 --> 00:27:34,160
 Do we really need another iPhone?

474
00:27:34,160 --> 00:27:37,700
 Right. Every year, a new iPhone comes out that promises to be bigger,

475
00:27:37,700 --> 00:27:41,100
 you know, faster, cooler, better performing than the previous one.

476
00:27:41,100 --> 00:27:43,700
 I don't know how much better it can actually get.

477
00:27:43,700 --> 00:27:45,600
 Right. When you have a supercomputer

478
00:27:45,600 --> 00:27:48,840
 in your pocket that can literally do anything you want.

479
00:27:49,140 --> 00:27:51,360
 And yet, because we want more, we want better.

480
00:27:51,360 --> 00:27:53,500
 Right. We think that the iPhone's old.

481
00:27:53,500 --> 00:27:56,100
 The last one's old, even though it just came out a few months ago.

